The contact information provided below is for some of the University's more critical offices.         If you are looking for a specific person or specific information at New York University, you can search for them in our online directories, or call the number listed to the right.     Student Information   University Development and Alumni Relations   University Relations and Public Affairs                      Student Information   The offices below cover a wide range of needs for prospective, incoming, and current students. If you're looking for information regarding taking a tour of NYU, financial aid, registration for classes, and paying your bill, the offices below can guide you.        Undergraduate Admissions   For information sessions and campus tours:   Jeffrey S. Gould Welcome Center  50 West Fourth Street  New York, NY 10003  212.998.4550  Weekdays: 9:00 AM to 5:00 PM  Saturday: 10:00 AM to 4:00 PM   For questions about admissions and to mail application materials:   665 Broadway, 11th Floor  New York, NY 10012  212.998.4500   admissions.ops@nyu.edu          Office of Financial Aid   25 West Fourth Street, 1st Floor  New York, NY 10012  212.998.4444  212.995.4661 (Fax)   financial.aid@nyu.edu   Office of the Registrar   25 West Fourth Street, 1st Floor  New York, NY 10012  212.998.4800 (University Registrar General Number)     Office of the Bursar   25 West Fourth Street, 1st Floor  New York, NY 10012  212.998.2800          The Student Resource Center   60 Washington Square South, Suite 210  New York, NY 10012  212.998.4411  Contact via email: Ask Us a Question        Student Health Center   726 Broadway, 3rd and 4th Floors  New York, NY 10003  212.443.1000   health.center@nyu.edu            University Development and Alumni Relations   NYU’s office of University Development and Alumni Relations (UDAR) focuses on the engagement of the entire NYU community – trustees, deans, students, faculty members, administration and staff, alumni, parents, and friends. If you have questions regarding alumni benefits or giving to the University, please contact UDAR and they can guide you.   UDAR Office   25 West Fourth Street, 4th Floor  New York, NY 10012  212.998.6900            University Relations and Public Affairs   University Relations and Public Affairs is responsible for ensuring that NYU’s message, agenda, and image are effectively and creatively projected to both external and internal audiences. If you have questions regarding NYU and its local community, photo or film shoots, or using the University's brand or identity, contact the offices below and someone will guide you in the right direction.
